\mt1 Joel
\c 1
\p \v 1 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* that came to Joel, the son of Pethuel:
\s1 An Invasion of Locusts
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt [Hos. 5:1] \x*Hear this, \x + \xo 1:2 \xt ver. 14 \x*you elders;
\q2 give ear, \x + \xo 1:2 \xt ver. 14 \x*all inhabitants of the land!
\q1 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt [ch. 2:2]\x*Has such a thing happened in your days,
\q2 or in the days of your fathers?
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Ps. 78:4]\x*Tell your children of it,
\q2 and let your children tell their children,
\q2 and their children to another generation.
\b
\q1
\v 4 What \x + \xo 1:4 \xt ch. 2:25; Amos 4:9 \x*the cutting locust left,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt [Amos 7:1]; See Ex. 10:4 \x*the swarming locust has eaten.
\q1 What the swarming locust left,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt ch. 2:25; Ps. 105:34; Nah. 3:15 \x*the hopping locust has eaten,
\q1 and what the hopping locust left,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt ch. 2:25; Ps. 78:46\x*the destroying locust has eaten.
\b
\q1
\v 5 Awake, you drunkards, and weep,
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:5 \xt [Isa. 24:11] \x*wail, all you drinkers of wine,
\q1 because of \x + \xo 1:5 \xt ch. 3:18; Isa. 49:26; Amos 9:13\x*the sweet wine,
\q2 for it is cut off from your mouth.
\q1
\v 6 For \x + \xo 1:6 \xt ch. 2:2 \x*a nation has come up against my land,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:6 \xt ch. 2:2 \x*powerful and beyond number;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [Rev. 9:7, 8]\x*its teeth are lions’ teeth,
\q2 and it has the fangs of a lioness.
\q1
\v 7 It has laid waste my vine
\q2 and splintered my \x + \xo 1:7 \xt [ver. 12]\x*fig tree;
\q1 it has stripped off their bark and thrown it down;
\q2 their branches are made white.
\b
\q1
\v 8 Lament like a virgin\f + \fr 1:8 \ft Or \fq young woman\f* \x + \xo 1:8 \xt [ver. 13]; See 2 Sam. 3:31\x*wearing sackcloth
\q2 for the bridegroom of her youth.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ver. 13; ch. 2:14 \x*The grain offering and the drink offering are cut off
\q2 from the house of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ch. 2:17; [Isa. 61:6; Ezek. 45:4]\x*The priests mourn,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ch. 2:17; [Isa. 61:6; Ezek. 45:4]\x*the ministers of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 10 The fields are destroyed,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:10 \xt See Hos. 4:3 \x*the ground mourns,
\q1 because \x + \xo 1:10 \xt [Hos. 2:9]\x*the grain is destroyed,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:10 \xt [Hos. 2:9]\x*the wine dries up,
\q2 the oil languishes.
\b
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt [Jer. 14:4] \x*Be ashamed,\f + \fr 1:11 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq dry up \ft and \fq be ashamed \ft in verses 10–12, 17 sound alike\f* O tillers of the soil;
\q2 wail, O vinedressers,
\q1 for the wheat and the barley,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt ver. 17\x*because the harvest of the field has perished.
\q1
\v 12 The vine dries up;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:12 \xt [ver. 7] \x*the fig tree languishes.
\q1 Pomegranate, palm, and apple,
\q2 all the trees of the field are dried up,
\q1 and \x + \xo 1:12 \xt Isa. 24:11; Jer. 48:33\x*gladness dries up
\q2 from the children of man.
\s1 A Call to Repentance
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [ver. 8; Jer. 4:8] \x*Put on sackcloth and lament, \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [See ver. 9 above] \x*O priests;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [ver. 8; Mic. 1:8] \x*wail, O ministers of the altar.
\q1 Go in, \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [ver. 8; Jer. 4:8] \x*pass the night in sackcloth,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [See ver. 9 above] \x*O ministers of my God!
\q1 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt ver. 9; ch. 2:14\x*Because grain offering and drink offering
\q2 are withheld from the house of your God.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt ch. 2:15, 16; See 2 Chr. 20:3 \x*Consecrate a fast;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt ch. 2:15, 16; See 2 Chr. 20:3 \x*call a solemn assembly.
\q1 Gather \x + \xo 1:14 \xt ver. 2\x*the elders
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:14 \xt ver. 2\x*all the inhabitants of the land
\q1 to the house of the \nd Lord\nd* your God,
\q2 and cry out to the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 15 Alas for the day!
\q1 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt ch. 2:1, 11, 31; 3:14; Isa. 13:6, 9; Jer. 46:10; Ezek. 30:2, 3; Amos 5:18; Obad. 15; Zeph. 1:14, 15; Zech. 14:1; 2 Pet. 3:10\x*For the day of the \nd Lord\nd* is near,
\q2 and as destruction from the Almighty\f + \fr 1:15 \fq Destruction \ft sounds like the Hebrew for \fq Almighty\f* it comes.
\q1
\v 16 Is not the food cut off
\q2 before our eyes,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:16 \xt [Deut. 12:6, 7; 16:14, 15]\x*joy and gladness
\q2 from the house of our God?
\b
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 1:17 \xt [Mal. 2:3] \x*The seed shrivels under the clods;\f + \fr 1:17 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew line is uncertain\f*
\q2 the storehouses are desolate;
\q1 the granaries are torn down
\q2 because \x + \xo 1:17 \xt ver. 11\x*the grain has dried up.
\q1
\v 18 How \x + \xo 1:18 \xt ch. 2:22; [Jer. 12:4; Hos. 4:3]\x*the beasts groan!
\q2 The herds of cattle are perplexed
\q1 because there is no pasture for them;
\q2 even the flocks of sheep suffer.\f + \fr 1:18 \ft Or \fq are made desolate\f*
\b
\q1
\v 19 To you, \x + \xo 1:19 \xt Ps. 50:15 \x*O \nd Lord\nd*, I call.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:19 \xt Jer. 9:10\x*For fire has devoured
\q2 the pastures of the wilderness,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:19 \xt Jer. 9:10\x*and flame has burned
\q2 all the trees of the field.
\q1
\v 20 Even the beasts of the field \x + \xo 1:20 \xt [Job 38:41; Ps. 104:21; 145:15] \x*pant for you
\q2 because the water brooks are dried up,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:20 \xt [See ver. 19 above]\x*and fire has devoured
\q2 the pastures of the wilderness.
\c 2
\s1 The Day of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q1 \v 1 \x + \xo 2:1 \xt ver. 15; Isa. 58:1; Hos. 5:8; Amos 3:6 \x*Blow a trumpet in \x + \xo 2:1 \xt See ch. 3:17 \x*Zion;
\q2 sound an alarm on \x + \xo 2:1 \xt See ch. 3:17 \x*my holy mountain!
\q1 Let all the inhabitants of the land tremble,
\q2 for \x + \xo 2:1 \xt See ch. 1:15\x*the day of the \nd Lord\nd* is coming; it is near,
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt Amos 5:18, 20; Zeph. 1:15 \x*a day of darkness and gloom,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt Amos 5:18, 20; Zeph. 1:15 \x*a day of clouds and thick darkness!
\q1 Like blackness there is spread upon the mountains
\q2 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt ch. 1:6; [ver. 11, 25] \x*a great and powerful people;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt [ch. 1:2]\x*their like has never been before,
\q2 nor will be again after them
\q2 through the years of all generations.
\b
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 2:3 \xt ch. 1:19, 20 \x*Fire devours before them,
\q2 and behind them a flame burns.
\q1 The land is like \x + \xo 2:3 \xt Gen. 2:8, 9; See Isa. 51:3 \x*the garden of Eden before them,
\q2 but \x + \xo 2:3 \xt Zech. 7:14\x*behind them a desolate wilderness,
\q2 and nothing escapes them.
\b
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 2:4 \xt Rev. 9:7\x*Their appearance is like the appearance of horses,
\q2 and like war horses they run.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 2:5 \xt Rev. 9:9; [Nah. 3:2] \x*As with the rumbling of chariots,
\q2 they leap on the tops of the mountains,
\q1 like the crackling of \x + \xo 2:5 \xt Isa. 5:24; 47:14; Obad. 18; Nah. 1:10 \x*a flame of fire
\q2 devouring the stubble,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:5 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*like a powerful army
\q2 drawn up for battle.
\b
\q1
\v 6 Before them peoples are in anguish;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:6 \xt Nah. 2:10\x*all faces grow pale.
\q1
\v 7 Like warriors they charge;
\q2 like soldiers they scale the wall.
\q1 They march each on his way;
\q2 they do not swerve from their paths.
\q1
\v 8 They do not jostle one another;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:8 \xt Prov. 30:27\x*each marches in his path;
\q1 they burst through the weapons
\q2 and are not halted.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 2:9 \xt Isa. 33:4 \x*They leap upon the city,
\q2 they run upon the walls,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:9 \xt [Jer. 9:21] \x*they climb up into the houses,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:9 \xt [Jer. 9:21] \x*they enter through the windows \x + \xo 2:9 \xt [John 10:1]\x*like a thief.
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt ch. 3:16; [Ps. 18:7; Amos 8:8] \x*The earth quakes before them;
\q2 the heavens tremble.
\q1 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt ch. 3:15; Isa. 13:10; Ezek. 32:7; Matt. 24:29; [Rev. 9:2]\x*The sun and the moon are darkened,
\q2 and the stars withdraw their shining.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt ch. 3:16; [1 Thess. 4:16] \x*The \nd Lord\nd* utters his voice
\q2 before \x + \xo 2:11 \xt ver. 25 \x*his army,
\q1 for his camp is exceedingly great;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt Rev. 18:8 \x*he who executes his word is powerful.
\q1 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt See ch. 1:15 \x*For the day of the \nd Lord\nd* is \x + \xo 2:11 \xt ver. 31 \x*great and very awesome;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt Mal. 3:2; [Num. 24:23]\x*who can endure it?
\s1 Return to the \nd Lord\nd*
\q1
\v 12 “Yet even now,” declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:12 \xt Deut. 4:30; 1 Sam. 7:3; Jer. 4:1; Hos. 12:6 \x*“return to me with all your heart,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:12 \xt [1 Sam. 7:6]\x*with fasting, with weeping, and with mourning;
\q2
\v 13 and \x + \xo 2:13 \xt [Ps. 34:18] \x*rend your hearts and not \x + \xo 2:13 \xt See Gen. 37:29 \x*your garments.”
\q1 Return to the \nd Lord\nd* your God,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:13 \xt Ex. 34:6; Ps. 86:5, 15; Jonah 4:2 \x*for he is gracious and merciful,
\q1 slow to anger, and abounding in steadfast love;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:13 \xt [Num. 23:19; Ezek. 24:14]\x*and he relents over disaster.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 2:14 \xt Jonah 3:9 \x*Who knows whether he will not turn and relent,
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:14 \xt Hag. 2:19; Mal. 3:10 \x*leave a blessing behind him,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:14 \xt ch. 1:9, 13\x*a grain offering and a drink offering
\q2 for the \nd Lord\nd* your God?
\b
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 2:15 \xt See ver. 1 \x*Blow the trumpet in Zion;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:15 \xt See ch. 1:14\x*consecrate a fast;
\q1 call a solemn assembly;
\q2
\v 16 gather the people.
\q1 \x + \xo 2:16 \xt See Josh. 3:5 \x*Consecrate the congregation;
\q2 assemble the elders;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:16 \xt [2 Chr. 20:13] \x*gather the children,
\q2 even nursing infants.
\q1 \x + \xo 2:16 \xt [Deut. 24:5; Eccles. 3:5; Zech. 12:12-14; 1 Cor. 7:5]\x*Let the bridegroom leave his room,
\q2 and the bride her chamber.
\b
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 2:17 \xt Ezek. 8:16 \x*Between the \x + \xo 2:17 \xt 1 Kgs. 6:3; 2 Chr. 3:4 \x*vestibule and the \x + \xo 2:17 \xt 2 Chr. 4:1 \x*altar
\q2 \x + \xo 2:17 \xt See ch. 1:9 \x*let the priests, the ministers of the \nd Lord\nd*, weep
\q1 and say, “Spare your people, O \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and make not your heritage a reproach,
\q2 a byword among the nations.\f + \fr 2:17 \ft Or \fq reproach, that the nations should rule over them\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 2:17 \xt Ps. 42:3; 79:10; 115:2\x*Why should they say among the peoples,
\q2 ‘Where is their God?’”
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Had Pity
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 2:18 \xt Zech. 1:14; 8:2 \x*Then the \nd Lord\nd* became jealous for his land
\q2 \x + \xo 2:18 \xt [Ps. 103:13]\x*and had pity on his people.
\q1
\v 19 The \nd Lord\nd* answered and said to his people,
\q1 “Behold, \x + \xo 2:19 \xt [ch. 1:10; Ps. 4:7]; See Mal. 3:10-12\x*I am sending to you
\q2 grain, wine, and oil,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:19 \xt [ch. 1:10; Ps. 4:7]; See Mal. 3:10-12\x*and you will be satisfied;
\q1 and I will no more make you
\q2 a reproach among the nations.
\b
\q1
\v 20 “I will remove the northerner far from you,
\q2 and drive him into a parched and desolate land,
\q1 his vanguard\f + \fr 2:20 \ft Hebrew \fq face\f* into \x + \xo 2:20 \xt Ezek. 47:18; Zech. 14:8 \x*the eastern sea,
\q2 and his rear guard\f + \fr 2:20 \ft Hebrew \fq his end\f* into \x + \xo 2:20 \xt Zech. 14:8 \x*the western sea;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:20 \xt Isa. 34:3; [Amos 4:10]\x*the stench and foul smell of him will rise,
\q2 for he has done great things.
\b
\q1
\v 21 “Fear not, O land;
\q2 be glad and rejoice,
\q2 for \x + \xo 2:21 \xt Ps. 126:2, 3\x*the \nd Lord\nd* has done great things!
\q1
\v 22 Fear not, \x + \xo 2:22 \xt See ch. 1:18 \x*you beasts of the field,
\q2 for \x + \xo 2:22 \xt [ch. 1:19] \x*the pastures of the wilderness are green;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:22 \xt [Zech. 8:12]\x*the tree bears its fruit;
\q2 the fig tree and \x + \xo 2:22 \xt [Zech. 8:12]\x*vine give their full yield.
\b
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23 \xt Ps. 100:1, 2; Hab. 3:18; Zech. 10:7 \x*“Be glad, O children of Zion,
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:23 \xt Ps. 100:1, 2; Hab. 3:18; Zech. 10:7 \x*rejoice in the \nd Lord\nd* your God,
\q1 for he has given \x + \xo 2:23 \xt Deut. 11:14; Jer. 5:24 \x*the early rain for your vindication;
\q2 he has poured down for you abundant rain,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:23 \xt Deut. 11:14; Jer. 5:24 \x*the early and \x + \xo 2:23 \xt Hos. 6:3\x*the latter rain, as before.
\b
\q1
\v 24 “The threshing floors shall be full of grain;
\q2 the vats shall overflow with wine and oil.
\q1
\v 25 I will restore\f + \fr 2:25 \ft Or \fq pay back\f* to you the years
\q2 that \x + \xo 2:25 \xt ch. 1:4 \x*the swarming locust has eaten,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:25 \xt ch. 1:4 \x*the hopper, \x + \xo 2:25 \xt ch. 1:4 \x*the destroyer, and \x + \xo 2:25 \xt ch. 1:4 \x*the cutter,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:25 \xt ver. 11\x*my great army, which I sent among you.
\b
\q1
\v 26 \x + \xo 2:26 \xt Lev. 25:19 \x*“You shall eat in plenty and be satisfied,
\q2 and praise the name of the \nd Lord\nd* your God,
\q2 who has dealt wondrously with you.
\q1 And my people \x + \xo 2:26 \xt [Isa. 49:23]\x*shall never again be put to shame.
\q1
\v 27 \x + \xo 2:27 \xt ch. 3:17 \x*You shall know that I am \x + \xo 2:27 \xt Hos. 11:9; See Ezek. 37:26 \x*in the midst of Israel,
\q2 and that \x + \xo 2:27 \xt See Ex. 20:2 \x*I am the \nd Lord\nd* your God \x + \xo 2:27 \xt [Isa. 44:8] \x*and there is none else.
\q1 And my people \x + \xo 2:27 \xt [See ver. 26 above]\x*shall never again be put to shame.
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Will Pour Out His Spirit
\q1
\v 28 \f + \fr 2:28 \ft Ch 3:1 in Hebrew\f* \x + \xo 2:28 \xt ver. 28-32, cited Acts 2:17-21 \x*“And it shall come to pass afterward,
\q2 that \x + \xo 2:28 \xt Isa. 32:15; Ezek. 39:29; Zech. 12:10; John 7:39 \x*I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:28 \xt [Acts 2:39] \x*your sons and \x + \xo 2:28 \xt [Acts 21:9]\x*your daughters shall prophesy,
\q2 your old men shall dream dreams,
\q2 and your young men shall see visions.
\q1
\v 29 \x + \xo 2:29 \xt [1 Cor. 12:13]\x*Even on the male and female servants
\q2 in those days I will pour out my Spirit.
\b
\p
\v 30 “And I will show \x + \xo 2:30 \xt [Matt. 24:30; Luke 21:11]\x*wonders in the heavens and \x + \xo 2:30 \xt [Matt. 24:30; Luke 21:11]\x*on the earth, blood and fire and columns of smoke.
\v 31 \x + \xo 2:31 \xt See ver. 10 \x*The sun shall be turned to darkness, \x + \xo 2:31 \xt Rev. 6:12 \x*and the moon to blood, \x + \xo 2:31 \xt Mal. 4:5\x*before the great and awesome day of the \nd Lord\nd* comes.
\v 32 And it shall come to pass that \x + \xo 2:32 \xt Cited Rom. 10:13 \x*everyone who calls on the name of the \nd Lord\nd* shall be saved. \x + \xo 2:32 \xt Isa. 46:13; 59:20; Obad. 17 \x*For in Mount Zion and in Jerusalem there shall be those who escape, as the \nd Lord\nd* has said, and among \x + \xo 2:32 \xt Jer. 31:7; Mic. 4:7; Zech. 8:12\x*the survivors shall be those whom the \nd Lord\nd* calls.
\c 3
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Judges the Nations
\p \v 1 \f + \fr 3:1 \ft Ch 4:1 in Hebrew\f* “For behold, \x + \xo 3:1 \xt Jer. 30:3\x*in those days and at that time, when I restore the fortunes of Judah and Jerusalem,
\v 2 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt [Zeph. 3:8]; See Zech. 14:2-4 \x*I will gather all the nations and bring them down to the Valley of Jehoshaphat. And \x + \xo 3:2 \xt Isa. 66:16; Jer. 25:31\x*I will enter into judgment with them there, on behalf of my people and my heritage Israel, because they have scattered them among the nations and have divided up my land,
\v 3 and \x + \xo 3:3 \xt Obad. 11; Nah. 3:10\x*have cast lots for my people, and have traded a boy for a prostitute, and have sold a girl for wine and have drunk it.
\p
\v 4 “What are you to me, \x + \xo 3:4 \xt Isa. 23:1, 2; Jer. 47:4; Amos 1:9 \x*O Tyre and Sidon, and all \x + \xo 3:4 \xt [Ezek. 25:15, 16] \x*the regions of Philistia? Are you paying me back for something? If you are paying me back, \x + \xo 3:4 \xt [Obad. 15]\x*I will return your payment on your own head swiftly and speedily.
\v 5 For \x + \xo 3:5 \xt [2 Chr. 21:16, 17]\x*you have taken my silver and my gold, and have carried my rich treasures into your temples.\f + \fr 3:5 \ft Or \fq palaces\f*
\v 6 You have sold \x + \xo 3:6 \xt [ver. 3]\x*the people of Judah and Jerusalem to the Greeks in order to remove them far from their own border.
\v 7 Behold, I will stir them up from the place to which you have sold them, and \x + \xo 3:7 \xt [See ver. 4 above]\x*I will return your payment on your own head.
\v 8 I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hand of the people of Judah, and they will sell them to the \x + \xo 3:8 \xt See 1 Kgs. 10:1\x*Sabeans, to a nation far away, for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken.”
\b
\q1
\v 9 Proclaim this among the nations:
\q1 \x + \xo 3:9 \xt [Mic. 3:5]\x*Consecrate for war;\f + \fr 3:9 \ft Or \fq Consecrate a war\f*
\q2 stir up the mighty men.
\q1 Let all the men of war draw near;
\q2 let them come up.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt [Isa. 2:4]\x*Beat your plowshares into swords,
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:10 \xt [Isa. 2:4]\x*your pruning hooks into spears;
\q2 let the weak say, “I am a warrior.”
\b
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 3:11 \xt [Isa. 54:15] \x*Hasten and come,
\q2 all you surrounding nations,
\q2 and gather yourselves there.
\q1 \x + \xo 3:11 \xt [Zech. 14:5]\x*Bring down your warriors, O \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 12 Let the nations stir themselves up
\q2 and come up to \x + \xo 3:12 \xt ver. 2 \x*the Valley of Jehoshaphat;
\q1 \x + \xo 3:12 \xt Ps. 96:13; 98:9; 110:6; Isa. 2:4; 3:13; Mic. 4:3\x*for there I will sit to judge
\q2 all the surrounding nations.
\b
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 3:13 \xt Rev. 14:15 \x*Put in the sickle,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:13 \xt [Jer. 51:33; Hos. 6:11; Matt. 13:30, 39; Mark 4:29; John 4:35; Rev. 14:15, 18] \x*for the harvest is ripe.
\q1 \x + \xo 3:13 \xt Rev. 14:20; [Isa. 63:2, 3]\x*Go in, tread,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:13 \xt Rev. 14:20; [Isa. 63:2, 3]\x*for the winepress is full.
\q1 The vats overflow,
\q2 for their evil is great.
\b
\q1
\v 14 Multitudes, multitudes,
\q2 in the valley of decision!
\q1 For \x + \xo 3:14 \xt See ch. 1:15\x*the day of the \nd Lord\nd* is near
